WEEK 1: FOUNDATION, ARCHITECTURE & DESIGN
Day 1: Core Repository Setup

[DevOps] Initialize Next.js 15 App Router: Setup with TypeScript, Tailwind, and ESLint.

[DevOps] Git Setup: Branch protection rules on main (require 1 PR approval).

[DevOps] Environment: Create .env.local template with empty variables for DB, Auth, and Razorpay.

[Frontend] Path Aliases: Configure tsconfig.json for clean imports (e.g., @/components, @/imports).

Day 2: State & Animation Infrastructure

[Frontend] Zustand Initialization: Create src/store/useCartStore.ts and useUIStore.ts.

[Frontend] Framer Motion Provider: Wrap the root layout in <AnimatePresence> for page transitions.

[Frontend] Global Scroll Context: Create a master useScroll hook at the top level so child components (like the Jacket and Scatter Reveal) can read the exact same scroll physics.

Day 3: Luxury Design System

[Design] ShadCN Initialization: Install and configure base components (Button, Sheet, Dialog, Input).

[Design] Typography & Colors: Add custom fonts (Serif/Sans) to tailwind.config.ts. Define Deep Onyx #0a0a0a and Off-White #f3f3f3.

[Frontend] Liquid Glass Utilities: Create reusable CSS classes for the text stroke, mix-blend-color-dodge, and drop-shadows used in your preloader.

Day 4: Global Layout & Stacking Context

[Frontend] Navbar: Build responsive header. Must be transparent at top of page, and blur/frost when scrolled.

[Frontend] Mobile Menu: Build full-screen slide-out menu with stagger animations for links.

[Architecture] Z-Index Master Document: Define strict z-index rules (e.g., Preloader: 50, Navbar: 40, ScatterReveal: 30, Background: 0).

Day 5: High-Performance Image Pipeline

[Backend] Cloudinary SDK: Install and configure Cloudinary.

[Frontend] <ImageWithFallback/> Component: Build a custom image wrapper that automatically requests .webp formats, lazy-loads, and shows a blurred placeholder while loading.

Day 6: Cinematic Intro Sequence (The "Wow" Factor)

[Frontend] Automated Preloader: Implement the 0-100 counter and "Pop and Stack" 3D card animation.

[Frontend] Split Jacket Hero: Implement the scroll-driven jacket opening.

[Frontend] Sequence Handoff: Use useMotionValueEvent to perfectly time the handoff from the jacket opening to the preloader wiping up.

Day 7: Physics & Frame Rate Tuning

[Frontend] 60fps Audit: Check animations on a physical mobile device.

[Frontend] Safari Address Bar Fix: Ensure 100vh doesn't glitch when mobile browser address bars shrink/grow (use dvh or adjust scroll triggers).

WEEK 2: DATABASE, IDENTITY & SECURITY
Day 8: Database Provisioning

[Database] PostgreSQL Setup: Provision DB (Vercel or Supabase).

[Database] Prisma Init: Connect Prisma to the database and generate initial client.

Day 9: Schema Design & Vector Prep

[Database] Core Models: Write Prisma schemas for User, Account, Session, Product, Variant (Size/Color), Order, OrderItem.

[Database] Advanced Schema: Add JSONB column to User for progressive profiling.

[Database] Migration: Add CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS vector; to the raw SQL migration for future AI features.

Day 10: Native Authentication

[Backend] Better Auth / Auth.js: Install and configure the core auth handler.

[Frontend] Auth UI: Build premium Login/Register forms with ShadCN inputs.

[Security] Password Hashing: Ensure bcrypt/argon2 is implemented for email/password signups.

Day 11: Social Identity

[DevOps] OAuth Keys: Generate Client IDs/Secrets for Google and Apple.

[Backend] Auth Providers: Add Google and Apple providers to Auth config.

[Database] Account Linking: Ensure if a user signs up with Email, and later clicks "Google" with the same email, the accounts merge gracefully.

Day 12: Security & Middleware

[Backend] Next.js Middleware: Create middleware.ts to block unauthenticated users from /account and /admin routes.

[Backend] Rate Limiting: Add basic rate-limiting to auth and checkout API routes.

[Backend] Zod Validation: Create strict Zod schemas for all API incoming payloads (prevent SQL injection/bad data).

Day 13: Customer Dashboard

[Frontend] Profile UI: Build the /account page layout.

[Backend] Server Actions: Build actions for users to update their name, phone, and default shipping address.

Day 14: Database Seeding (Crucial)

[Backend] seed.ts Script: Write a script to wipe the DB and insert 20 high-quality dummy products (jackets, tees, accessories) with real Cloudinary URLs, prices, and stock counts.

WEEK 3: COMMERCE ENGINE & SHOPPING
Day 15: Product Data Fetching

[Backend] Product API: Create Server Actions to fetch products. Include logic to fetch related products based on tags/categories.

Day 16: Product Listing Page (PLP)

[Frontend] Catalog Grid: Build the /shop page with a masonry or strict grid layout.

[Frontend] Filters: Implement client-side URL search params for filtering by category, price, and sorting (Newest, High-Low).

Day 17: Product Details Page (PDP)

[Frontend] Image Gallery: Build sticky image gallery on the left, scrollable product details on the right.

[Frontend] Variant Selector: Build size/color selectors. Must disable sizes where stock === 0.

Day 18: Instant Search Overlay

[Frontend] Search UI: Build full-screen blurred search overlay.

[Backend] Debounced Query: Implement a custom hook to wait 300ms after the user stops typing before querying the database.

Day 19: Optimistic Cart Architecture

[Frontend] Zustand Cart Wire-up: Connect the "Add to Cart" button to useCartStore.

[Frontend] Slide-out Cart: Build the Cart Sheet. Update totals and quantities instantly in the UI.

[Backend] Cart Sync: Write logic to sync the local Zustand cart with the database when the user logs in.

Day 20: Wishlist & Micro-interactions

[Frontend] Heart Toggle: Build animated heart icon (Framer Motion scale spring).

[Backend] Wishlist API: Save liked products to the database profile.

Day 21: End-to-End Commerce QA

[Testing] Flow Check: Verify the journey from Homepage -> Search -> PDP -> Cart -> Checkout button works without a single console error or hydration mismatch.

WEEK 4: PAYMENTS, ADMIN & LAUNCH
Day 22: Razorpay & Secure Webhooks

[Frontend] Razorpay SDK: Integrate the Razorpay checkout script/modal.

[Backend] Order Creation: Create order in DB as PENDING before opening Razorpay.

[Backend] Webhook Listener: Build /api/webhooks/razorpay to cryptographically verify payment success and update order to PAID.

Day 23: Transactional Messaging

[Backend] Resend Integration: Add API keys.

[Design] React Email: Design a premium, black-and-white HTML email template for "Order Confirmed".

[Backend] Trigger: Fire the email from the Razorpay success webhook.

Day 24: Customer Order History

[Frontend] Orders UI: Build the /account/orders view. Show order status badges (Paid, Processing, Shipped) and item breakdowns.

Day 25: Admin Command Center Shell

[Backend] RBAC: Update middleware to strictly require role === 'ADMIN' for /admin routes.

[Frontend] Admin Layout: Build a dense, desktop-optimized sidebar layout for the owner dashboard.

Day 26: Admin - Product Management

[Frontend] Product Forms: Build forms to Create/Edit products.

[Backend] Cloudinary Widget: Integrate direct-to-Cloudinary upload widget so owners can easily add product images from the browser.

Day 27: Admin - Order Fulfillment

[Frontend] Orders Table: Build a data table (ShadCN) of all incoming orders.

[Backend] Fulfillment Action: Build Server Action to input a tracking number, change status to SHIPPED, and trigger the shipping confirmation email.

Day 28: Logging & Analytics

[Frontend] Dashboard Stats: Aggregate DB data to show "Total Revenue," "Orders this Month," and "Low Stock Alerts."

[DevOps] Error Tracking: Install Sentry or Vercel Analytics to catch bugs automatically.

Day 29: Production Deploy & Environment

[DevOps] Vercel Deploy: Push to production.

[DevOps] Environment Audit: Ensure Razorpay is in Live mode, correct production DB URL is set, and Auth URLs point to your real domain (e.g., damagedgoods.com).

Day 30: Launch & Live QA

[Testing] Live Transaction: Buy a $1 item using a real credit card to ensure Webhooks and Emails fire in production. (Refund it immediately in Razorpay).

[Testing] Lighthouse: Run Chrome Lighthouse audit for SEO and Accessibility scores.

[Launch] Market the MVP.